            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>salmon fillet[s] </strong>to the other side of the tray[s], then add a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Season the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> with a pinch of<strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 12-15 min or until the salmon is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1718618814861-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
